response: A Hague adoption follows the process according to The Hague Adoption Convention, which is an international treaty used to ensure the best interests of the children, birth parents, and adoptive parents involved in the international adoption process. Most international adoptions are conducted ethically, but in Hague-compliant countries, there is less room for corruption to take place. Want to hear more?
